          <h2>Research &amp; work in progress</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div class="pub-meta">
            <h3>History of Nosara <span class="pub-badge">In progress</span></h3>
            <div class="pub-source">Editorial project - Multi-year - Oral history, archive and genealogy</div>
            <p>A book-length history of the district of Nosara, combining archival research (national archive, judicial records, vital statistics) with oral history interviews of the founding criollo families and the post-1968 settlement period. First book-length community history of the district.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div class="pub-meta">
            <h3>Sustainable &amp; Regenerative Development for Nosara <span class="pub-badge">In progress</span></h3>
            <div class="pub-source">Applied research - 2026 - ADC</div>
            <p>Building on the Census and the Fiscal Balance, this study tests models of territorial reordering that fit the data: water carrying capacity, housing density, public infrastructure ratios and economic diversification away from tourism-construction dependency.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div class="pub-meta">
            <h3>Territorial Fiscal Balance - methodology replication <span class="pub-badge">In progress</span></h3>
            <div class="pub-source">Methodology - 2026 - JP Asesores</div>
            <p>Documenting and packaging the Territorial Fiscal Balance methodology so it can be replicated by other districts and municipalities in Costa Rica and Central America. Open methodology, auditable sources, transferable workflow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div class="pub-meta">
            <h3>Digital Twins, Heat Maps &amp; Policy for the Future <span class="pub-badge">In progress</span></h3>
            <div class="pub-source">R&amp;D - 2026 - JP Asesores / ADC</div>
            <p>Real-time territorial digital twins, heat maps and policy simulation tools to anticipate and design futures for districts and municipalities. Integrates SIG cartography, demographic data, fiscal indicators and citizen-sourced signals into a single interactive layer.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="pub-item">
          <div class="pub-meta">
            <h3>Agentic, Internet-AI Native Institutions <span class="pub-badge">In progress</span></h3>
            <div class="pub-source">Applied research - 2026 - JP Asesores</div>
            <p>Designing institutions from scratch for the era of agentic AI and an internet-native public: governance models that assume continuous data flow, autonomous agents and distributed decision-making. Applied to local governments, community organizations and impact-driven ventures.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

